cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV. 

The paper proposes a method for multi-task reinforcement learning and continual reinforcement learning, which are both subfields of reinforcement learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper also uses a robot to navigate in a 2D environment, which suggests that it may fall under cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper involves state representation learning and policy distillation, which are techniques commonly used in the field of control systems, falling under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper uses simulated environments and real-life experiments, which may fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves perception and interpretation of visual data.
